{{Infobox software | name = EasyChair | screenshot = | caption = | developer = [[Andrei Voronkov]] | latest_release_version = | latest_release_date = | programming language = [[Perl]] | operating_system = [[Linux]] | genre = [[Academic conference]] [[abstract management]] | license = }} '''EasyChair''' is a free web-based [[Event management software|conference management software]] system<ref>{{Cite book | last1 = Cristo | first1 = P. | last2 = Martinho | first2 = R. | chapter = AEMS: Towards an Advanced Event Management System | doi = 10.1007/978-3-642-24355-4_9 | title = ENTERprise Information Systems | series = Communications in Computer and Information Science | volume = 220 | pages = 82 | year = 2011 | isbn = 978-3-642-24354-7 | pmid = | pmc = }}</ref><ref>[http://lasecwww.epfl.ch/pub/lasec/doc/LPG07.pdf Swee-Won Lo, Raphael C.-W. Phan, and Bok-Min Goi: On the Security of a Popular Web Submission and Review Software (WSaR) for Cryptology Conferences]: Comparison of EasyChair with other related systems (Appendix C, Related work). Workshop on Information Security Applications, 2007.</ref> used, among other tasks, to organise paper submission and review. EasyChair is widely used in the scientific community, with reportedly more than one million users in 2014.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Kanav|first1=Sudeep|last2=Lammich|first2=Peter|last3=Popescu|first3=Andrei|editor1-last=Biere|editor1-first=Armin|editor2-last=Bloem|editor2-first=Roderick|title=Computer Aided Verification - 26th International Conference|chapter=A Conference Management System with Verified Document Confidentiality|date=2014|publisher=Springer|series=LNCS|volume=8559|isbn=978-3-319-08866-2|pages=167–183}}</ref>
The EasyChair website also provides an [[open access]] online publication service for [[conference proceeding]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://easychair.org/publications/EPiC/Computing|title=EPiC Series in Computing|publisher=EasyChair}}</ref> When launched, in 2012, the service was for [[computer science]] only, but in 2016 it was expanded to all sciences.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://easychair.org/news_item.cgi?id=1718654659|title=EasyChair EPiC Series Opens for Areas Other than Computing|date=17 Jan 2016|publisher=EasyChair}}</ref>
The EasyChair software has been in continuous development since 2002. {{asof|2015}}, the code base consist of nearly 300,000 lines of code, and it has been used by more than 41,000 conferences.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Voronkov|first1=Andrei|editor1-last=Bjørner|editor1-first=Nikolaj|editor2-last=Prasad|editor2-first=Sanjiva|editor3-last=Parida|editor3-first=Laxmi|title=Distributed Computing and Internet Technology - 12th International Conference, ICDCIT 2016|date=2015|publisher=Springer|isbn=978-3-319-28033-2|pages=IVI-XVII|chapter=The Design of EasyChair|series=LNCS|volume=9581}}</ref>
It is similar to other event management [[system software]] such as [[OpenConf]] and is hosted by the [[School of Computer Science, University of Manchester|computer science department]] of the [[University of Manchester]].{{citation needed|date=June 2017}} It is owned by an English company.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://easychair.org/contact.cgi|title=Contacting EasyChair|website=easychair.org|language=en-US|access-date=2017-06-03}}</ref>
